# Scrollbar & Header-Sync – NICHT ÄNDERN

Dieser Fix verhindert, dass die Scrollbar beim Header-Umschalten (sticky/compact) springt oder länger wird.

## Nie entfernen oder ändern

### 1. CSS-Variablen auf Body (style.css)
```css
body {
  --gk-main-padding-top: 8rem;
  --gk-front-padding-top: 0;
}
body.gk-header-scrolled {
  --gk-main-padding-top: 12rem;
  --gk-front-padding-top: 4rem;
}
```

### 2. site-main liest Variablen + Transition (style.css)
```css
.site-main {
  padding-top: var(--gk-main-padding-top, 8rem);
  transition: padding-top 0.16s ease-out;
}
.site-main--front {
  padding-top: var(--gk-front-padding-top, 0);
}
```

### 3. site-header-inner Transition (style.css)
```css
.site-header-inner {
  transition: height 0.16s ease-out, min-height 0.16s ease-out;
}
```

### 4. Header-Scroll Hysterese (header-scroll-blur.js)
- `SCROLLED_PX = 24` – Hysterese, verhindert Hin-und-Her-Springen
- `CONSECUTIVE_TICKS_SCROLLED = 2`
- Wheel-Handler prüft `y >= SCROLLED_PX`

### 5. Account Scroll-Kompensation (account-dashboard.css)
```css
body.gk-header-scrolled.woocommerce-account.logged-in .site-main {
  padding-top: 4rem !important;
}
```

## Regel
Header-Höhe (8.5rem→4.5rem) und site-main padding-top (8rem→12rem) müssen **immer synchron** bleiben. Beide brauchen die gleiche Transition (0.16s ease-out).
